  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Procurement) (Up to $4500 / 5 days / City Hall)",
  "description": "<p>Job Title: Quantity Surveyor (Procurement) (ID6012)<br />Location: City Hall<br />Working Hour：Monday- Friday : 8:30am-5:30pm<br />Salary:$3600-$4500<br /><br />Roles & Responsibilities<br />• Coordinate procurement activities, including requesting quotations, price comparisons, negotiations, purchase orders, and documentation.<br />• Assist in developing and monitoring site budgets to ensure expenses stay within allocated limits.<br />• Maintain pricing database for trades and update RPO and future budget rates.<br />• Review quotations to identify exclusions and prevent additional costs.<br />• Track trade award status, update master programme, and coordinate with site staff.<br />• Compile project statistics, record site expenses, and ensure proper cost substantiations.<br />• Draft general correspondence and support team collaboration to achieve departmental targets.<br /><br />Requirement<br />• 3 years with a leading Singapore main building construction firm<br />• Coordinated procurement activities across projects, including requesting quotations, conducting price comparisons, and negotiating terms<br />• Processed purchase orders and managed all post-award procurement documentation<br />• Negotiated pricing, terms, and conditions prior to contract awards to ensure best value</p>",
